# Methodology

*AI Journey Map — v1.0 — June 26, 2026*

---

## What this document is

This file documents the intellectual foundations of the AI Journey Map project. It explains why the extraction rules are designed the way they are, what research they draw from, and what the project honestly cannot claim. Read this before reading `extraction-rules.md`.

---

## What this project is and is not

This is a longitudinal field study of one person's evolving relationship with AI technology. It is not a productivity log. It is not a portfolio. It is not a neutral record.

The narrator is both researcher and subject. Every voice note is already filtered through memory, mood, and the intent to record. The raw data is not neutral — it never was. That is not a flaw. It is the nature of first-person longitudinal research, and acknowledging it is what makes the study honest rather than naive.

---

## Reflexivity statement

The following biases are known, declared, and treated as variables — not hidden assumptions to be corrected away.

The narrator is a designer with over fifteen years of cross-disciplinary practice, working in English as a second language with French as the primary cognitive register. She has a prior positive disposition toward AI — not uncritical, but not sceptical by default. Her professional identity is oriented around building and systems-thinking, which shapes what she notices, what she finds worth recording, and how she frames what she records.

The extraction skill introduces a second layer of interpretation — a language model deciding what constitutes a beat, which quote carries it, and what emotion label fits. The rules in `extraction-rules.md` are designed to constrain this interpretation as tightly as possible. Judgment calls remain.

The bilingual dimension is an intentional variable, not noise. How ideas surface differently in English expression versus French cognitive structure is part of what this study is watching for over time.

This project does not claim objectivity. It claims honesty about its constraints.

